entry.def: Rung is the past participle of ring .
The rungs on a ladder are the wooden or metal bars that form the steps.

example.ex: I swung myself onto the ladder and felt for the next rung.
example.tran: 我纵身跳到梯子上，摸索着下一根横档。

entry.tran: (事业、组织、进程中的)级别，等级，地位
entry.def: If you reach a particular rung in your career, in an organization, or in a process, you reach that level in it.

example.ex: I first worked with him in 1971 when we were both on the lowest rung of our careers...
example.tran: 我第一次和他共事是在1971年，那时我们的事业都刚刚起步。

example.ex: There has never been a better time to get on the first rung of the property ladder.
example.tran: 迈出置业第一步的最佳时机莫过于此。
